# ReadMe

The whole package includes two directories (database for database and templates for web pages) and a main file named app2.py


Database Directory:
It contains the project database.


Templates Directory:
It contains three files: index.html, result.html and error.html
	-- index.html: main operation page;
	-- result.html: result page;
	-- error.html: error page when encounter errors


Main File:
app2.py


Usage Instruction:
in the termianl: python app2.py ;
then copy and paste the link "http://127.0.0.1:5000" in browser;
press ctrl+C to quit;


Operation Instructions:
1. Select
    1.1 Table Selection: Select table;
    1.2 Column Info: Enter column name;
    1.3 Where Condition (Optional): Enter filters;
2. Insert
    2.1 Table Selection: Select table;
    2.2 Values Info: Enter insert value, if it is a varchar type value, make sure using single quotation marks '';
3. Update
    3.1 Table Selection: Select table;
    3.2 Reset Condition: Enter update logic;
    3.3 Where Condition (Optional): Enter filters;
4. Delete
    4.1 Table Selection: Select table;
    4.2 Where Condition (Optional): Enter filters;
5. Create
    5.1 Table Name: Enter table name;
    5.2 Column & Type Info: Enter column name and its type;
6. Set Operation
    6.1 Table1 Selection: Select table;
    6.2 Table2 Selection: Select table;
    6.3 Table Operation: Choose the operation method;
    6.4 Column Info: Columns for final result;
    6.5 Join Column for table1: Columns for join operation;
    6.6 Join Column for table2: Columns for join operation;
7. Set Comparison
    7.1 Table1 Selection: Select table;
    7.2 Table2 Selection: Select table;
8. Set Membership
    8.1 Table Selection: Select table;
    8.2 Column Info: Columns for final result;
    8.3 Column Selection: Columns for where condition;
    8.4 Values Info: Values for where condition;
9. CTE(With Clause)
  CTE Part:
    9.1 CTE Name: Table name;
    9.2 Table Selection: Select table;
    9.3 Column Selection: Select Only One column here;
    9.4 Where Condition (Optional): Enter filters;
  Select Part:
    9.5 Table Selection: Select table;
    9.6 Column Info: Columns for final result;
10. Aggregation Function
    10.1 Aggregation Method: Choose the method;
    10.2 Table Selection: Select table;
    10.3 Column Info: Columns for final result;
    10.4 Aggregation Column: Column used in aggregate function;
    10.5 Partition By: Columns for partition;
    10.6 Order By: Columns for order;
    10.7 Range (Optional): Rows;
11. OLAP Function
    11.1 Table Selection: Select table;
    11.2 Column Info: Columns and aggregation for final result;
    11.3 Group Condition: Group columns;


Kindly Reminder:
If the database cannot be connected in your local environment, please change the username and password in line 7/48/116 in the app2.py.
(The code is: conn = pymysql.connect(host='127.0.0.1',...) )